  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Peace Education for Colombian children</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Inequality and acts of direct violence present in much of Colombia increase in territories with fewer economic resources. In these places, children are constantly exposed to scenes of violence, micro-trafficking and other activities that put them at risk. For 10 years, TECHO Colombia&apos;s peace education program has worked with approximately 260 children and adolescents a year, who live in poverty, providing analytical skills so that they can discern and make decisions about their reality.</narrative>
  </description>
